                                                       2-7-1996@{ub}
@endnode

@node "gb.introduction" "Introduction ot cryptography"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.requirements"
@prev "gb.disclamer"
 @{b}@{u}"It's personal.  It's private.  And it's no one's business but yours."@{ub}@{uu}

  This abstract was taken from @{b}PGP@{ub}'s user manual by @{b}Phil Zimmermann@{ub}. It describes on of the main reason for using a cryptography system. That's it: @{b}@{fg shine}PRIVACY@{ub}@{fg text}.

  How many times did you ever wished that there was somehow a way to pass some information to someone, without the risk of someone stealing it?

  Fear no more! @{b}@{fg shine}HideIt@{ub}@{fg text} is here!

  HideIt is a @{i}NEW@{ui} cryptographic program especially designed for the @{fg shine}Amiga@{fg text}. This means that it rovides the safety of equivallent cryptography systems (such as PGP), but using an intuitive and smart @{i}user interface@{ui}.

  HideIt shares the same encyption algorithm as PGP from Phil Zimmermann does; that is the @{b}RSA@{ub} algorithm. However, HideIt provides you with more security via another algorihm the @{b}DES@{ub}, which is used in top of RSA.

  Special care was taken to ensure that this program is Amiga @{i}native@{ui}, by providing the user with a powerfull @{b}GUI@{ub}. The user can @{i}encrypt/decrypt@{ui} files with a few mouse clicks; never cryptography was so easy to use. Also, the program provides a comprehensive @{i}on-line help@{ui} facility, which makes the program even easier to use, especially for starters.
@endnode

@node "gb.requirements" "Software Requirements"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.usage"
@prev "gb.introduction"
  To operate this program, you need:

@{b}  - An Amiga or DraCo compatible computer.
  - KickStart v2.04 or newer.
  - 256KB memory.@{ub}

  The program makes use of some features available in the latest versions of the operating system (@{b}3.0/3.1@{ub}), such as @{i}NewMenus@{ui} and @{i}memory pools@{ui}.
@endnode

@node "gb.usage" "Usage"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.closewindow"
@prev "gb.requirements"
  This program comes in five versions: one for @{b}68000@{ub} CPUs, one for @{b}68020@{ub} CPUs, one for @{b}68030@{ub} CPUs with @{b}68882@{ub} FPU, one for @{b}68040@{ub} CPUs and one for @{b}68060@{ub} CPUs.

  When you double click on the program's icon, a window like the following one will appear on the @{i}Workbench@{ui} Screen:



           @{"o" link "gb.closewindow" 0}-HideIt Workbench @{"vX.X" link "gb.versionid" 0}---------------------@{"{}" link "gb.move" 0}+
           |                                             |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.encrypt" 0}              +-------------+ @{"+-+" link "gb.input" 0}  |
           | @{"|Encrypt|" link "gb.encrypt" 0}  @{"I" link "gb.input" 0}nput File  |             | @{"|»|" link "gb.input" 0}  |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.encrypt" 0}              +-------------+ @{"+-+" link "gb.input" 0}  |
           |                                             |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.decrypt" 0}             +-------------+ @{"+-+" link "gb.output" 0}   |
           | @{"|Decrypt|" link "gb.decrypt" 0} O@{"u" link "gb.output" 0}tput File |             | @{"|»|" link "gb.output" 0}   |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.decrypt" 0}             +-------------+ @{"+-+" link "gb.output" 0}   |
           |                                             |
           |                       +-----------------+   |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.start" 0}   P@{"a" link "gb.password" 0}ssword  |                 |   |
           | @{"| Start |" link "gb.start" 0}             +-----------------+   |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.start" 0}                                   |
           |                                             |
           | Algorithm                                   |
           |                                             |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.rsa" 0}                                   |
           | @{"|@| RSA |" link "gb.rsa" 0}                                   |
           | @{"+-------+" link "gb.rsa" 0}                                   |
           |                                             |
           +---------------------------------------------+


 The program has the following menu, which is shown when you move the pointer to the screen bar and @{i}hold down the right mouse button@{ui}:


            HideIt Menu ==========+
