@node "gb.encrypt" "Encrypt"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.decrypt"
@prev "gb.move"
  Here you select that you want to encrypt the file specified in the
  @{"Input" link "gb.input" 0} string.

  @{"Return" link "gb.usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.decrypt" "Decrypt"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.input"
@prev "gb.encrypt"
 Here you select that you want to decrypt the file specified in the @{"Input" link "gb.input" 0}
 string, to the file specified in the @{"Output" link "gb.output" 0} string.

 @{"Return" link "gb.main" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.input" "Input String"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.output"
@prev "gb.decrypt"
  Here you select the input file in which the specified @{b}Encrypt@{ub} or @{b}Decrypt@{ub} action will be performed.

  - Click on the "»" button to specify the file with the ASL file requester.
  - Press the "I" key or click inside the string gadget, to type the
    filename.

 @{fg shine} For safety reasons, the specified filename will be shown ONLY when you click inside
  the string gadget.@{fg text}

  @{"Return" link "gb.usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.output" "Output"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.password"
@prev "gb.input"
  Here, you can select the name of the @{b}output file@{ub} to be (de)crypted.

  - Press on the "»" button, to select the file via the ASL file requester.
  - Click inside the string field (or press the "u" key) to type the
    output filename.

  The same safety rules apply here, as described in the @{"Input Field" link "gb.input" 0} section.

  @{"Return" link "gr.uses" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.password" "Password"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.start"
@prev "gb.output"
  You can enter here, the @{b}base@{ub} keyword that will be used by the program internally, to produce additional (de)encryption codes.

  The same safety rules apply here, as described in the @{"Input Field" link "gb.input" 0} section.

  @{"Return" link "gb.usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.start" "Start Process"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.rsa"
@prev "gb.password"
  Clicking here, the (de)coding process begins, according the data contained in the @{"Input" link "gb.input" 0}, @{"Output" link "gb.output" 0}, @{"Password" link "gb.password" 0} and @{"Algorithm" link "gb.rsa" 0} fields. After completion, the program returns information about the success (or failure) of the procedure and also information of the time it took to take place.

 @{"Return" link "gb.usage" 0}
@endnode

@node "gb.rsa" "RSA & DES"
@toc "gb.main"
@next "gb.help"
@prev "gb.start"
  Here you can select the required algorithm to be used in the @{b}encryption@{ub} process. Note that the selection here is required @{u}only when encrypting data@{uu} and not while decrypting, since in the decryption the program seeks and selects the correct algorithm used on encryption.

  The program supports two encrypting algorithms:

 @{b} - RSA
  - RSA & DES@{ub}

  The RSA algorithm is used by other programs too, such as@{b} PGP@{ub} by Phil Zimmerman. It provides excellent protection against hacking and it is said to be extremely time consuming - not to say @{i}impossible@{ui} - to crack. This is the default selected algorithm by @{i}HideIt@{ui}.

  The second option is exactly the same as the first, except that after the data are encrypted with RSA are re-encrypted with the DES algorithm also, @{i}in top of the RSA@{ui}. This option is provided for all hack-scared out there, in order to ensure further security; however @{i}it takes more time@{ui} to complete than the first option.
@endnode

@node "gb.help" "Online Help"
@toc "gb.main"
@prev "gb.rsa"
  With this option, you enable the on-line built-in help. From now on, instead of performing the requested command, the program returns information about the selected option.

  Select this option again, to turn off help.

 @{" Return" link "gb.usage" 0}
@endnode

